  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational dataset collected across five clinical perfusion sites, capturing in-service hemolysis indices under varied flow-speed combinations. The observational study is cited throughout the credibility narrative as the primary experimental basis for the validation claim, and its breadth of real-world operating conditions is presented as strengthening the relevance of the validation activities to the COU. The requirement governing this validation activity, however, specifies that hemolysis-index verification must be performed via a controlled experiment in which flow rate, rotational speed, and blood analog properties are independently varied under laboratory conditions with a single test article — a protocol that an observational study, by design, cannot fulfill.",
