      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison against multisite observational data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against hemolysis indices recorded in the multisite observational study spanning five clinical CPB perfusion centres. Across all five flow-speed operating points, predicted RH values remained below 1.0, consistent with the observational cohort median. The observational dataset encompassed 312 patient-perfusion episodes with concurrent pump flow and speed logging, providing a statistically robust reference population. Agreement between CFD predictions and observed haemolysis indices was within ±12% across all operating points, which the assessment team judged to satisfy the acceptance criterion. The activity underpinning this result is classified as an observational study because data were collected from routine clinical practice without prospective randomisation or controlled variation of individual input parameters.",
