        "name": "Multisite clinical observational study of CPB hemolysis indices",
        "description": "Retrospective and concurrent collection of hemolysis index measurements from five clinical perfusion centres operating the FDA generic centrifugal pump design. Data collection covered 312 perfusion episodes over 18 months. Flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) were logged from pump consoles; plasma free haemoglobin was measured at standardised intervals. No experimental manipulation of pump parameters was performed; operating conditions reflected routine clinical decision-making by perfusionists.",
